data.text:
The Lebanese recording artist, Dominique Hourani, is also an actress, beauty queen and former model. Her first breakthrough was when she first appeared on TV in the series Oyoun Kha’ena (The eyes of the deceiver), where she acted alongside the famous TV presenter, Tony Khalife.

Later, Hourani was offered a role for her first movie, El Beeh Romancy, to act with famous actors like Mohoamed Adel Emam, Hasan Housni, Lebleba, Saad El Soghair and Mena Arafa. In the Arab world, Hourani remains a famous figure not only through her acting career but also through her singing career. Hourani sang in the live concert organized for Arab Americans, where there were more than 300,000 people attending. So far, Hourani has launched three albums, Etriss in 2006, Kermalik Ya Dominique in 2008 and Dominique in 2011. Hourani also

won the Miss Intercontinental 2003 title in a competition with over 80 countries participating. She was married two times and has a daughter with her second husband who was Iranian-Dutch businessman. Currently, Dominique Hourani is single and lives in the United Arab Emirates (UAE). After enjoying so much success in career that is still at its heights, Dominique Hourani will go from strength to strength. We look forward to seeing the wonderful new projects that await this incredibly gifted artist.
